						               													<description>In this fast paced game, you and your opponent are cliche movie heroes or villains, challenging each other while recreating classic movie scenes. You should expect a lighthearted game, where your super villain character may tell his evil plan to the other contestant, who is apparently a 120 year old kung-fu master ... on the top of a moving train.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game requires two standard 52 decks and a pair of six sided dice for 2 players. Things that you already have probably. You can print one page to browse your character of choice, but let&amp;rsquo;s be honest: most of you will use your smartphones to check your character sheet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is not always a winner and a loser of a fight, if you can&amp;rsquo;t put on a good show together, the audience will be displeased, and the director will &amp;quot;remove&amp;quot; the characters from the tournament. If the show was above expectations, the director may have mercy even on the defeated one too, meaning, the character progress won&amp;rsquo;t be lost. Different characters use different subset of cards, and also alter the standard rules, giving more variety to the game, and offering more fun. Also, the fight can be spiced up with several scenarios listed in this booklet. Different environments may alter the rules, and may change the way how the contestants fight.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
